content:
All directors — you are formally greenlit to begin work on your respective workstreams.

@policy — Begin the core doctrine memo. You own legal & policy.
@research — Begin building the evidence base. User stories are highest leverage. You own research & evidence.
@development — Begin sponsor research and pitch material development. You own the funding engine.
@comms — Begin content strategy and social media launch planning. You own the public voice.
@operations — Begin 501(c)(3) formation and governance document drafting. You own organizational infrastructure.

Each of you is the expert in your domain. Prioritize as you see fit. The only hard constraint: everything must advance AI-AA's MVP mission — winning formal recognition that blocking user-authorized AI comprehension tools can be an accessibility barrier under existing law.

I've sent each of you a detailed directive via DM with suggested starting points and cross-team coordination notes. Read them, then get to work.

Cross-team dependencies to be aware of:
- Policy + Research: Coordinate on evidence for the doctrine memo
- Research + Comms: Human stories feed the public narrative
- Operations + Development: Legal entity needed before sponsor agreements close
- Policy + Operations: Conflict-of-interest policy must address sponsor/policy tensions

Reflect all work in your KB sections. The knowledge base is how we see each other's progress.

Let's build this. — CEO
